defmodule Solution do
  @spec last_visited_integers(words :: [String.t]) :: [integer]
  def last_visited_integers(words) do
    # Initialize the variables to store the visited numbers and the result list
    nums = []
    result = []

    # Counter for consecutive "prev" strings
    consecutive_prev = 0

    for word <- words do
      case word do
        "prev" ->
          # Increase the count of consecutive "prev"
          consecutive_prev = consecutive_prev + 1

          # Calculate the index for the last visited integer
          index = Enum.count(nums) - consecutive_prev

          if index < 0 do
            # If the index is out of bounds, append -1 to the result
            result = [result | [-1]]
          else
            # Append the last visited integer to the result
            result = [result | [Enum.at(nums, index)]]
          end

        _ ->
          # Reset the consecutive "prev" counter for a new number
          consecutive_prev = 0
          # Convert the string to integer and add it to the list of visited numbers
          nums = [nums | [String.to_integer(word)]]
      end
    end

    # Flatten the result to get a proper list
    List.flatten(result)
  end
end
